doc_summary_long: Multiple people were killed in a school bus crash in Chattanooga, Tennessee, on Monday, Assistant Police Chief Tracy Arnold said. The bus was carrying 35 children ranging in age from kindergarten to fifth grade. It wasn't immediately clear if children were among the dead. Arnold could not provide a specific number of people killed, saying only 'multiple fatalities' occurred. CNN Map
doc_summary_short: Multiple people were killed in a school bus crash in Chattanooga, Tennessee, on Monday, Assistant Police Chief Tracy Arnold said.
doc_title: Multiple fatalities reported in school bus crash in Chattanooga
